Iron and Oak Railroad Services | LinkedIn Skip to main content LinkedIn Top Content People Learning Jobs Games Join now Sign in Iron and Oak Railroad Services Construction Iron and Oak Railroad Services, Ensuring Your Business Never Goes Off Track Follow Discover all 8 employees Report this company About us At Iron and Oak Railroad Services our team greatly emphasizes strong relationships at every point of contact. We utilize our communication, project management, and construction knowledge to assist customers in meeting the requirement of their tracks. 

Iron and Oak Railroad Services differ from other Rail Contractors as we strive to build a long-term maintenance plan for our customers. A plan based on customers budgets, shut down schedules, long-term logistics goals, consistent track safety improvements and more.

In order to assess your track and provide pricing for track maintenance and construction we offer complimentary site visits to meet and provide our recommendations. Please contact harlee@ironandoakrail.com to book anytime or call 905-979-5387. 

We look forward to the opportunity to quote your business and working together in the future. 

Visit www.ironandoakrail.com to learn more. I hope you have a chance to visit www.ironandoakrail.com to see for yourself. We look forward to working together in the future and thank you to all of our valued customers! #railroadcontractor #canadiancompany #supportlocal #diversityandinclusion #essentialworkers 9 1 Comment Like Comment Share Iron and Oak Railroad Services reposted this Harlee Barfknecht-zuber Director of Business Development 9mo Report this post I am beyond grateful that my work in building Iron and Oak Railroad Services has earned the emerging business award for the WIBA‚Äôs presented by the @the_gncc  and sponsored by the Niagara Economic Development. 

The rain this week affected production on a track maintenance job for one of our customers and every one of my crew is here on a Saturday to complete the job without hesitation. 

I‚Äôm surrounded by harder workers and it inspires me to stand tall and confident in my role as owner and operator. 

Thank you to my crew, my customers, and my suppliers, for the opportunity to start my own company. I look forward to doing business with all of you for years to come. #wiba2024 #emergingbusiness #railroadcontractor #essentialworkers #diversityandinclusion #teamwork #grateful 114 16 Comments Like Comment Share Iron and Oak Railroad Services 784 followers 10mo Report this post Congratulations to our Director and CEO Harlee Barfknecht-zuber on being nominated for the Emerging business award by the Women In Niagara council of the Greater Niagara Chamber of Commerce for all her work here at Iron and Oak Railroad Services ! 

If you would like to attend the awards follow the link https://lnkd.in/g7MhcNz5 and we look forward to seeing you there! #WIBA2024 #railroaders #diversityandinclusion #emergingbusiness #growthanddevelopment Harlee Barfknecht-zuber Director of Business Development 10mo I‚Äôm thrilled to announce I have been named a finalist for Women In Niagara emerging business award for Iron and Oak Railroad Services ! 

I‚Äôm so proud of the work we do and a heartfelt thank you to everyone that championed my nomination. Submitting those letters made me feel like I already won. 

I look forward to attending this event and cheering on my fellow finalist. If you too would like attend tickets are available https://lnkd.in/giZxuJPQ .

We have it all! see menu book your event The Iron Oak Post building was Melbourne's 5th post office from the 1920's until the 1950's.
